🧠 What “Block Mapping” Means
👉 Block Mapping = translating file data → actual disk location

Logical Block  →  Physical Block
(file view)       (disk reality)
📦 Step-by-Step Intuition
1. File is just a stream of bytes
When you read a file:

file.txt → "Hello World..."
Kernel sees it as:

Offset 0, 1, 2, 3...
2. Filesystem divides file into blocks
Example (block size = 4KB):

File:
[Block 0] [Block 1] [Block 2] ...
These are called:

👉 Logical Blocks (file-relative)

3. Disk has its own layout
Disk looks like:

[Block 500] [Block 501] [Block 900] [Block 1200] ...
👉 These are Physical Blocks (real storage locations)

🔑 Block Mapping = Connecting These Two
Filesystem (like ext4) maintains a mapping:

Logical Block 0 → Physical Block 900
Logical Block 1 → Physical Block 901
Logical Block 2 → Physical Block 1200
